Durban - Police visited a shooting scene on Wednesday where a  32-year-old man was found with gunshot wounds to his head in Phoenix. Captain Nqobile Gwala, a KwaZulu Natal Police spokesperson, said the shooting occurred on Tuesday afternoon and Phoenix police station was made aware of the shooting incident on Wednesday. Prem Balram, private security company Reaction Unit South Africa spokesperson, said paramedics were called out to the scene after the man collapsed on the roadside. "Medics treated him for two gunshot wounds to his head before transporting him to a hospital in a critical condition. The motive for the shooting is subject to investigation however it is alleged that the man was a victim of a robbery. Several individuals confirmed that they had heard gunshots shortly before the victim emerged from a canal and collapsed on the roadside bleeding extensively from his head," Balram said. Gwala said police are appealing for anyone with information to contact 10111. Daily News